    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-16T00:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-16T00:30:00-05:00" n="342"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d342">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">788.00/8–1653: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 342<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran (<persName corresp="#p_MGH1" type="from"
                            >Mattison</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d342fn1">Repeated to London and Beirut for Ambassador
                            <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">Henderson</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted<lb/>
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-16T09:00:00+03:30"
                            >August 16, 1953—9 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>331. At early hour this morning Embassy received reports of confusing nature to
                    effect that Shah had issued decree removing <persName corresp="#p_MM1"
                        >Mosadeq</persName> as Prime Minister and that resultant activity had
                    involved various troop movements and arrests in Tehran. At 7 a.m. Radio Tehran
                    announced <hi rend="italic">coup d’état</hi> against <persName corresp="#p_MM1"
                        >Mosadeq</persName> government had been attempted last night and had been
                    successfully thwarted by government. Information received by Embassy at about
                    same time tended confirm fact government had situation under control.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_ARMISH1">ARMISH</gloss> has been informed <persName
                        corresp="#p_RBGT1">General Riahi</persName>, Chief of Staff, under orders
                    Prime Minister has arrested three of five brigade commanders Tehran garrison and
                        <persName corresp="#p_KGA1">General Kiani</persName>, Assistant Chief of
                    Staff. Meeting at Iranian officers club now in progress presided by <persName
                        corresp="#p_RBGT1">General Riahi</persName> attended by general
                    officers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MGH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mattison</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
